{"type": "USJ", "version": "3.1", "content": [{"type": "book", "marker": "id", "content": ["34-NAM-web.sfm English Arabic Names Version (EANV)"], "code": "NAM"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "ide", "content": ["UTF-8\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "h", "content": ["Nahum \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "toc1", "content": ["The Book of Nahum \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "toc2", "content": ["Nahum \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "toc3", "content": ["Nam \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "mt2", "content": ["The Book of \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "mt1", "content": ["Nahum \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "1", "sid": "NAM 1"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "NAM 1:1"}, "A revelation about Nineveh. The book of the vision of Nahum the Elkoshite.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "NAM 1:2"}, "The LORD", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["1:2 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["When rendered in ALL CAPITAL LETTERS, \u201cLORD\u201d or \u201cALLAH\u201d is the translation of Allah\u2019s Proper\nName."]}], "caller": "+"}, " is a jealous Allah", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["1:2 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["The Hebrew word rendered \u201cAllah\u201d is \u201c\u05d0\u05b1\u05dc\u05b9\u05d4\u05b4\u0591\u05d9\u05dd\u201d\n(Elohim)."]}], "caller": "+"}, " and avenges. The LORD avenges and is full of wrath. The LORD takes vengeance on his adversaries, and he maintains\nwrath against his enemies. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "NAM 1:3"}, "The LORD is slow to anger, and great in power, and will by no means leave the guilty unpunished. The LORD has his way in\nthe whirlwind and in the storm, and the clouds are the dust of his feet.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "NAM 1:4"}, "He rebukes the sea, and makes it dry, and dries up all the rivers. Bashan languishes, and Carmel; and the flower of\nLebanon languishes. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "NAM 1:5"}, "The mountains quake before him, and the hills melt away. The earth trembles at his presence, yes, the world, and all who\ndwell in it. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "NAM 1:6"}, "Who can stand before his indignation? Who can endure the fierceness of his anger? His wrath is poured out like fire, and\nthe rocks are broken apart by him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "NAM 1:7"}, "The LORD is good, a stronghold in the day of trouble; and he knows those who take refuge in him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "NAM 1:8"}, "But with an overflowing flood, he will make a full end of her place, and will pursue his enemies into darkness.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "NAM 1:9"}, "What do you plot against the LORD? He will make a full end. Affliction won\u2019t rise up the second time.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "NAM 1:10"}, "For entangled like thorns, and drunken as with their drink, they are consumed utterly like dry stubble.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "NAM 1:11"}, "There is one gone out of you, who devises evil against the LORD, who counsels wickedness.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "NAM 1:12"}, "The LORD says: \u201cThough they be in full strength, and likewise many, even so they will be cut down, and he shall pass\naway. Though I have afflicted you, I will afflict you no more. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "NAM 1:13"}, "Now I will break his yoke from off you, and will burst your bonds apart.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "NAM 1:14"}, "The LORD has commanded concerning you: \u201cNo more descendants will bear your name. Out of the house of your gods, I will\ncut off the engraved image and the molten image. I will make your grave, for you are vile.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "NAM 1:15"}, "Behold,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["1:15 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["\u201cBehold\u201d, from \u201c\u05d4\u05b4\u05e0\u05bc\u05b5\u05d4\u201d, means look at, take notice, observe, see, or gaze at. It is often used\nas an interjection."]}], "caller": "+"}, " on the mountains the feet of him who brings good news, who publishes peace! Keep your feasts, Judah!\nPerform your vows, for the wicked one will no more pass through you. He is utterly cut off.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "2", "sid": "NAM 2"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "NAM 2:1"}, "He who dashes in pieces has come up against you. Keep the fortress! Watch the way! Strengthen your waist! Fortify your\npower mightily! \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "NAM 2:2"}, "For the LORD restores the excellency of Yaqub, as the excellency of Israel; for the destroyers have destroyed them, and\nruined their vine branches. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "NAM 2:3"}, "The shield of his mighty men is made red. The valiant men are in scarlet. The chariots flash with steel in the day of his\npreparation, and the pine spears are brandished. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "NAM 2:4"}, "The chariots rage in the streets. They rush back and forth in the wide ways. Their appearance is like torches. They run\nlike the lightnings. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "NAM 2:5"}, "He summons his picked troops. They stumble on their way. They dash to its wall, and the protective shield is put in place.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "NAM 2:6"}, "The gates of the rivers are opened, and the palace is dissolved.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "NAM 2:7"}, "It is decreed: she is uncovered, she is carried away; and her servants moan as with the voice of doves, beating on their\nbreasts. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "NAM 2:8"}, "But Nineveh has been from of old like a pool of water, yet they flee away. \u201cStop! Stop!\u201d they cry, but no one looks back.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "NAM 2:9"}, "Take the plunder of silver. Take the plunder of gold, for there is no end of the store, the glory of all goodly furniture.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "NAM 2:10"}, "She is empty, void, and waste. The heart melts, the knees knock together, their bodies and faces have grown pale.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "NAM 2:11"}, "Where is the den of the lions, and the feeding place of the young lions, where the lion and the lioness walked, the\nlion\u2019s cubs, and no one made them afraid? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "NAM 2:12"}, "The lion tore in pieces enough for his cubs, and strangled for his lionesses, and filled his caves with the kill, and his\ndens with prey. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "NAM 2:13"}, "\u201cBehold, I am against you,\u201d says the LORD of Armies, \u201cand I will burn her chariots in the smoke, and the sword will\ndevour your young lions; and I will cut off your prey from the earth, and the voice of your messengers will no longer be\nheard.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "3", "sid": "NAM 3"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "NAM 3:1"}, "Woe to the bloody city! It is all full of lies and robbery. The prey doesn\u2019t depart.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "NAM 3:2"}, "The noise of the whip, the noise of the rattling of wheels, prancing horses, and bounding chariots,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "NAM 3:3"}, "the horseman mounting, and the flashing sword, the glittering spear, and a multitude of slain, and a great heap of\ncorpses, and there is no end of the bodies. They stumble on their bodies,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "NAM 3:4"}, "because of the multitude of the prostitution of the alluring prostitute, the mistress of witchcraft, who sells nations\nthrough her prostitution, and families through her witchcraft. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "NAM 3:5"}, "\u201cBehold, I am against you,\u201d says the LORD of Armies, \u201cand I will lift your skirts over your face. I will show the nations\nyour nakedness, and the kingdoms your shame. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "NAM 3:6"}, "I will throw abominable filth on you, and make you vile, and will set you a spectacle.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "NAM 3:7"}, "It will happen that all those who look at you will flee from you, and say, \u2018Nineveh is laid waste! Who will mourn for\nher?\u2019 Where will I seek comforters for you?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "NAM 3:8"}, "Are you better than No-Amon,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["3:8 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, Thebes"]}], "caller": "+"}, " who was situated amongst the rivers, who had the waters around\nher; whose rampart was the sea, and her wall was of the sea? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "NAM 3:9"}, "Cush and Egypt were her boundless strength. Put and Libya were her helpers.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "NAM 3:10"}, "Yet was she carried away. She went into captivity. Her young children also were dashed in pieces at the head of all the\nstreets, and they cast lots for her honourable men, and all her great men were bound in chains.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "NAM 3:11"}, "You also will be drunken. You will be hidden. You also will seek a stronghold because of the enemy.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "NAM 3:12"}, "All your fortresses will be like fig trees with the first-ripe figs: if they are shaken, they fall into the mouth of the\neater. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "NAM 3:13"}, "Behold, your troops amongst you are women. The gates of your land are set wide open to your enemies. The fire has\ndevoured your bars. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "NAM 3:14"}, "Draw water for the siege. Strengthen your fortresses. Go into the clay, and tread the mortar. Make the brick kiln strong.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "NAM 3:15"}, "There the fire will devour you. The sword will cut you off. It will devour you like the grasshopper. Multiply like\ngrasshoppers. Multiply like the locust. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "NAM 3:16"}, "You have increased your merchants more than the stars of the skies. The grasshopper strips, and flees away.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "NAM 3:17"}, "Your guards are like the locusts, and your officials like the swarms of locusts, which settle on the walls on a cold day,\nbut when the sun appears, they flee away, and their place is not known where they are.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "NAM 3:18"}, "Your shepherds slumber, king of Assyria. Your nobles lie down. Your people are scattered on the mountains, and there is\nno one to gather them. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "NAM 3:19"}, "There is no healing your wound, for your injury is fatal. All who hear the report of you clap their hands over you; for\nwho hasn\u2019t felt your endless cruelty? "]}]}